[Cumulatively, 14.7 percent of total males are MSM (men who have sex with men); 2.9 percent of the total are healthcare workers, and 4.7 percent of the total are food handlers. More cases continue to occur, spreading north and west of the main southeastern Michigan focus of the outbreak. The total of cases continues to increase, although at a lower rate, and in numbers and fatalities has altogether surpassed the numbers of the now essentially ended southern California outbreak.

